text.paragraph:
The most common adverse reactions with Gabapentin in combination with other antiepileptic drugs in pediatric patients 3 to 12 years of age, not seen at an equal frequency among placebo-treated patients, were viral infection, fever, nausea and/or vomiting, somnolence, and hostility [see 



                               Warnings and Precautions (5.7) 
                           ].
